H0.text: In chemistry, what are elements called when they have a greater atomic number than uranium. Posturanic

H1.text: In chemistry, what are elements called when they have a greater atomic number than uranium. Hyperuranic

H2.text: In chemistry, what are elements called when they have a greater atomic number than uranium. Uraniumplus

H3.text: In chemistry, what are elements called when they have a greater atomic number than uranium. Transuranic

A4.text: The transuranium (or transuranic) elements are the chemical elements with atomic number greater than 92, which is the atomic number of uranium.
